org.opendaylight.controller.md.sal.dom.store.impl.tree

Class ListenerTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opendaylight.controller.md.sal.dom.store.impl.tree.ListenerTree

  • public final class ListenerTree
extends java.lang.Object
    A set of listeners organized as a tree by node to which they listen. This class allows for efficient lookup of listeners when we walk the DataTreeCandidate.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  ListenerTree.Node
      This is a single node within the listener tree.
      static class  ListenerTree.Walker
      A walking context, pretty much equivalent to an iterator, but it exposes the underlying tree structure.

      • getWalker

        public ListenerTree.Walker getWalker()
        Obtain a tree walking context. This context ensures a consistent view of the listener registrations. The context should be closed as soon as it is not required, because each unclosed instance blocks modification of the listener tree.
        Returns:
        A walker instance.
